<chapter>
<title>Documentation without Copyright</title>
<section>
<title>What is Documentation without Copyright?</title>
<body>

<p>
<e>Documentation without Copyright</e> is documentation of which we don't have
the copyright but we can do whatever we want with the documentation as
long as whe adhere to certain rules. Most of these documents are articles that
<mail link="drobbins@gentoo.org">Daniel Robbins</mail> wrote for the IBM
DeveloperWorks website.
</p>

<p>
The restriction is that we must mention who owns the article and where
they originally appeared. For instance:
</p>

<pre caption = "Restriction Paragraph">
&lt;section&gt;
&lt;title&gt;About this document&lt;/title&gt;
&lt;body&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
The original version of this article was first published on IBM
developerWorks, and is property of Westtech Information Services. This
document is an updated version of the original article, and contains
various improvements made by the Gentoo Linux documentation team.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;
</pre>

</body>
